{"batch":"Abstractions & Dependencies","batch_index":1,"assessments":{"abstraction_fitness":64.5},"dimension_notes":{"abstraction_fitness":{"evidence":["`StartupRuntime` is split into multiple callback bags (`startupInitRuntime`, `startupBootstrapRuntime`, `startupSwapRuntime`) with many nil-guard forwarding methods that add little domain behavior, e.g. `InitializeConfig`, `InitializeAuth`, `InitializeRouter`, `InitializeDocker` in `goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go:109-214`.","`startBackgroundServicesRuntime` continues the same pattern with six embedded callback structs plus parallel `validate()` scans of function pointers (`goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go:346-549`), and tests must construct large function matrices (`goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator_test.go:105-211`).","Docker orchestration has overlapping seam layers: `Runtime*Ops` groups in `goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_ops.go:11-94` and separate `dockerRuntime*` groups in `goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_docker.go:141-204`, both wiring many function fields to mostly direct delegates (`goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_docker.go:206-290`).","Global config is still pulled directly inside collectors/runtime code (`config.StartramSettingsSnapshot`, `config.GetStartramConfig`, `config.BasePath`) in `goseg/broadcast/collectors/collectors.go:61-74,158`, while large mutable config models (`structs.SysConfig`) remain broad (`goseg/structs/configs.go:9-60`), weakening boundary-focused abstractions."],"impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","confidence":"high","sub_axes":{"abstraction_leverage":58.0,"indirection_cost":38.0,"interface_honesty":60.0}}},"findings":[{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"startup_callback_matrix_indirection","summary":"Startup orchestration uses oversized callback-bag abstractions that increase indirection and test setup without adding cohesive policy boundaries.","related_files":["goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go","goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator_test.go","goseg/main.go"],"evidence":["`startupInitRuntime` defines 13 function fields and then wraps each with near-identical nil checks and pass-through calls (`goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go:109-214`).","`startBackgroundServicesRuntime` embeds six more callback groups and validates each member separately (`goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go:346-549`), creating a second callback matrix in the same module.","Tests build large callback literals to satisfy abstraction shape rather than behavior (e.g. `startBackgroundServicesRuntime{...}` in `goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator_test.go:105-211`).","`main` introduces another wrapper layer (`bootstrapRuntime`, `bootstrapOrchestratorRuntime`, `bootstrapServerRuntime`, `bootstrapConnectivityRuntime`) that largely forwards to orchestrator/server functions (`goseg/main.go:59-111`)."],"suggestion":"Collapse callback bags into a smaller set of behavior-oriented interfaces (for example `SubsystemInitializer`, `BackgroundServiceStarter`, `ServerBootstrapper`) and move optional hooks into explicit option structs so tests override only capabilities they exercise; remove repetitive one-method forwarding wrappers once call sites use those interfaces directly.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"function_pointer_bag_overuse"},{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"runtime_seams_duplication_orchestration","summary":"Docker runtime seams are duplicated across multiple runtime types, creating parallel abstractions with overlapping contracts.","related_files":["goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_ops.go","goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_docker.go","goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_seams_test.go","goseg/docker/orchestration/wireguard.go"],"evidence":["`RuntimeContainerOps`/`RuntimeUrbitOps`/`RuntimeConfigOps` etc are defined in `runtime_ops.go:11-94`, while `runtime_docker.go` defines another family (`dockerRuntimeContextOps`, `dockerRuntimeConfigOps`, `dockerRuntimeWireguardOps`, etc.) in `runtime_docker.go:141-204`.","`newDockerRuntime` wires many fields by direct delegation (e.g., `config.BasePath`, `config.Architecture`, `config.DebugMode`, `config.GetWgConf`, `config.SetMinIOPassword`) with little adaptation (`runtime_docker.go:206-290`).","`WireguardRuntime` is a third seam bag with overlapping concerns (`StartContainerFn`, file ops, config access) and additional wrapper callback `WriteWgConfFn func(WireguardRuntime) error` (`runtime_docker.go:30-49,76` and used in `wireguard.go:25-30`).","Tests mirror this complexity with many stub adapters and no-op wrappers to satisfy seam shapes (`runtime_seams_test.go:15-293`)."],"suggestion":"Consolidate to one seam model per use case: keep a single `RuntimeDeps` contract for orchestration flows and compose narrow nested interfaces for file/docker/config concerns; remove duplicate `dockerRuntime*` vs `Runtime*Ops` layers and eliminate self-referential callbacks like `WriteWgConfFn(func(WireguardRuntime) error)` in favor of direct method injection.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"function_pointer_bag_overuse"},{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"config_boundary_leakage","summary":"Modules that define runtime abstractions still bypass them and read global config snapshots directly, making seams leaky and reducing abstraction honesty.","related_files":["goseg/broadcast/collectors/collectors.go","goseg/rectify/rectify.go","goseg/importer/importer.go","goseg/config/config.go","goseg/structs/configs.go"],"evidence":["`collectorRuntime` injects many dependencies, but `constructPierInfo` still reads globals directly (`config.StartramSettingsSnapshot`, `config.GetStartramConfig`) instead of routing through runtime (`collectors.go:61-74`).","`localBackupsForPeriod` reaches global runtime context (`config.BasePath`) directly within collectors (`collectors.go:158`), further mixing runtime seams with ambient state.","`RectifyRuntime` and `importerRuntime` are built as dependency carriers, yet defaults heavily bind to config singletons (`rectify.go:67-89`, `importer.go:96-115`) and methods fall back to package globals (`rectify.go:92-96`).","Underlying config model remains a broad mutable aggregate (`structs.SysConfig` has many unrelated concerns in `structs/configs.go:9-60`), encouraging snapshot/bag passing instead of bounded domain ports."],"suggestion":"Enforce seam purity at module boundaries: require all external state reads via injected runtime interfaces, remove direct `config.*` calls from runtime-aware functions, and split `SysConfig`-derived access into domain-specific providers (networking, startram, backup, runtime context) so consumers cannot depend on monolithic config state.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"global_config_as_param_bag"},{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"micro_runtime_wrappers_low_leverage","summary":"Several local runtime wrappers are thin nil-default layers that add boilerplate indirection without meaningful policy encapsulation.","related_files":["goseg/system/wifi.go","goseg/docker/network/network.go","goseg/main_test.go"],"evidence":["`wifiRuntime` + `withWiFiRuntime` manually merge six function pointers (`wifi.go:31-72`), then exported functions call `defaultWiFiService()` wrappers (`wifi.go:312-338`), adding call depth for mostly direct command execution.","`NetworkRuntime` repeats `runtime = runtime.withDefaults()` at the top of each method (`network.go:42,77,97,115,132,155,177`) instead of centralizing defaults at construction.","Tests in adjacent modules frequently build custom runtime structs solely to toggle one behavior, indicating abstraction shape cost (e.g., multiple runtime literals in `main_test.go:131-200`)."],"suggestion":"Prefer constructor-time dependency objects with required fields and small optional options structs; avoid per-call `withDefaults()` and default wrapper fan-out by constructing fully initialized services once and passing them through explicit module entry points.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"function_pointer_bag_overuse"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["Function-pointer bag pattern is used as the default abstraction mechanism across orchestration modules, causing contract sprawl.","Global config state remains broadly accessible, so newer runtime seams are only partially enforced."],"likely_symptoms":["startup_callback_matrix_indirection","runtime_seams_duplication_orchestration","micro_runtime_wrappers_low_leverage"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}
